Catahoula first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusLA>{{Cite web|title= 2010 Census of Population - Population and Housing Unit Counts - Louisiana |url=https://www2.census.gov/library/publications/decennial/2010/cph-2/cph-2-20.pdf|website=[[United States Census Bureau]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240402175429/https://www2.census.gov/library/publications/decennial/2010/cph-2/cph-2-20.pdf| archive-date=April 2, 2024}}</ref> 

The 2019 census estimates determined 1,054 people lived in Catahoula, spread over a total area of {{Convert|3.1|sqmi|km2}}.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=Geography Profile: Catahoula CDP, Louisiana|url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/profile?g=1600000US2213330|url-status=live|access-date=2021-07-31|website=data.census.gov|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210623030916/https://data.census.gov/cedsci/profile?g=1600000US2213330 |archive-date=2021-06-23 }}</ref> The racial and ethnic makeup of the census-designated place was 99.1% [[Non-Hispanic whites|non-Hispanic white]], and 0.9% [[Asian Americans|Asian]]. The median age was 38.4 and 19.7% spoke another language other than [[English language|English]] at home. The median household income was $52,417 and 11.5% of the population lived at or below the poverty line.

